address2: 8th Floor District 8, SCBD Lot 13 Jl. Jenderal Sudirman Kav. 52-53
longBusinessSummary: PT Bank QNB Indonesia Tbk provides various banking products and services in Indonesia. The company offers savings, checking, current, and multi-currency accounts; and time deposits, as well as loan products. It also provides mutual funds, such as equity, money market, fixed income, and balance funds; bancassurance services; cash management and trade finance services; and mobile and online banking, and ATM services. The company was formerly known as PT Bank QNB Kesawan Tbk and changed its name to PT Bank QNB Indonesia Tbk in July 2014. The company was founded in 1913 and is headquartered in Jakarta, Indonesia. PT Bank QNB Indonesia Tbk operates as a subsidiary of Qatar National Bank (Q.P.S.C.).
